<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Saurma</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-14"><hi rend="italic">October 14,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 11th instant, wherein you set forth the
                            probable cost of deportation of Mataafa and his eleven followers to
                            Jaluit, one of the Marshall Islands, and of their maintenance
                            thereon.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>